Date: 1998-03-23

Title: Two-point Functions in Affine Current Algebra and Conjugate Weights

Comments: 9 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A13 (1998) 1281-1288

The two-point functions in affine current algebras based on simple Liealgebras are constructed for all representations, integrable or non-integrable.The weight of the conjugate field to a primary field of arbitrary weight isimmediately read off.